## 4. Target Hyper Hybrid Shape

Future target:

```text
Archivezip/
- apps/
  - desktop/
  - frontend/
- services/
  - agent/
- packages/
  - shared-types/
  - ui/                 # future only, if UI primitives become cross-app
  - config/             # future only, if shared config grows
  - core/               # future only, if pure TS domain logic is reused
  - testing/            # future only, if test fixtures/helpers are reused
- crates/
  - hotpath/
  - shared-native/      # future only, if Rust helpers are reused beyond hotpath
- scripts/
- tools/                # future only, if build/dev automation becomes large
- doc/
  - dev/
  - architecture/       # future optional, if architecture docs grow
- testsprite_tests/
- e2e/                  # future optional, curated product E2E tests
- attached_assets/
- generated/            # future optional, central generated report/artifact zone
```

Important: this target tree is a roadmap, not an immediate move request.

Only create new packages when there is a clear reason:

- code is reused by two or more owners
- the package has a stable API
- the package can be tested independently
- the package can avoid importing application-specific state
- the package has a clean build/test command

