## 5. Ownership Map

### `apps/frontend`

Owns:

- visible IDE UI
- React component composition
- frontend state and client workflows
- command palette UI
- agent panel presentation
- editor, terminal, search, SCM, problems, settings, sessions UI
- Tauri bridge calls from the renderer
- HTTP/SSE client usage
- frontend tests

Must not own:

- Python agent orchestration
- provider implementations
- backend persistence
- filesystem trust enforcement as the only security layer
- shared schema source of truth
- release packaging rules

Allowed dependencies:

- `@zoc-studio/shared-types`
- frontend-local modules under `apps/frontend/src/lib`
- Tauri API wrappers through `tauri-bridge`
- backend only through typed client/API contracts

### `apps/desktop`

Owns:

- Tauri app shell
- native window startup
- sidecar lifecycle
- native filesystem IPC
- workspace root scope guard
- secure secrets
- native search/git/patch commands
- bundled binary configuration
- platform icons and Tauri capabilities

Must not own:

- React UI state
- agent reasoning/orchestration
- provider-specific LLM logic
- generated shared schema source

Allowed dependencies:

- `crates/hotpath`
- Tauri plugins
- narrow shared Rust dependencies from root `Cargo.toml`

### `services/agent`

Owns:

- FastAPI app and versioned API routes
- agent orchestration loop
- planner behavior
- Ask/Agent/Plan/Debug backend behavior
- tool registry and tool execution
- provider registry and provider adapters
- persistence and sessions
- approvals and permissions
- events/SSE stream
- indexing and recall
- project rules
- checkpoints and workspace diff
- backend tests

Must not own:

- frontend rendering choices
- Tauri-native window behavior
- shared schema TypeScript generation output as source of truth
- release packaging outside sidecar concerns

Allowed dependencies:

- `packages/shared-types/python`
- internal agent modules
- hotpath through the CLI bridge
- provider libraries

### `crates/hotpath`

Owns:

- Rust helper library and CLI
- PTY helpers
- file watching
- fast search
- chunking
- patch helpers
- native indexing helpers

Must not own:

- frontend UI
- Python API routes
- agent prompts
- product workflow state

Allowed dependencies:

- Rust workspace dependencies
- no frontend or Python imports

### `packages/shared-types`

Owns:

- cross-language API and event contracts
- Pydantic schema source of truth
- generated TypeScript type surface
- schema generation scripts

Must not own:

- frontend UI behavior
- backend business logic
- desktop IPC implementation
- provider logic

Rule:

```text
Python Pydantic models first -> generated TypeScript types second
```

### Future `packages/ui`

Create only if:

- more than one app needs the same UI primitives
- components are free of app-specific store state
- styles are token-driven
- package can have its own tests/stories

Do not move `features/*` into `packages/ui`.

Candidate contents:

- pure button/card/dialog wrappers
- design tokens
- typography primitives
- icon-button patterns
- reusable empty/loading/error states

### Future `packages/core`

Create only if:

- pure TypeScript logic is reused by multiple apps/packages
- code has no React, Tauri, browser-only, or backend-only dependency
- test coverage can be package-local

Candidate contents:

- path helpers
- pure diff utilities
- command metadata types
- validation helpers
- pure state machines

### Future `packages/config`

Create only if:

- lint, TypeScript, Tailwind, Vite, or test config is duplicated
- config can be shared without hiding important per-app differences

Candidate contents:

- shared ESLint config
- shared TS config base
- shared Prettier config
- shared test config helpers

### `scripts` and future `tools`

`scripts` owns small command-line automation.

Create `tools` only if:

- build/release/dev tooling becomes too large for scripts
- tooling needs tests
- tooling becomes a real package or CLI

Do not create `tools` for one-off shell scripts.

### `doc`

Owns:

- architecture plans
- roadmap documents
- implementation notes
- security/trust docs
- feature design docs

Recommended doc split:

```text
doc/
- *.me                 # broad planning and project strategy
- dev/                 # feature implementation docs
- architecture/        # future optional architecture decisions
```

### `testsprite_tests` and future `e2e`

`testsprite_tests` owns generated or imported product tests.

Create `e2e` only if:

- tests are curated and maintained by the project
- tests run as part of normal CI
- tests are not temporary generated artifacts

