## 6. Dependency Direction Rules

Hard rules:

- `packages/shared-types` must not depend on `apps`.
- `packages/shared-types` must not depend on `services`.
- `apps/frontend` must use backend APIs through typed contracts.
- `apps/frontend` must not import Python internals.
- `apps/desktop` must expose narrow IPC commands only.
- `apps/desktop` must not become a general backend.
- `services/agent` owns orchestration, providers, tools, and persistence.
- `crates/hotpath` stays native/performance-focused.
- `scripts` must not become runtime product code.

Preferred direction:

```text
packages/shared-types/python
  -> packages/shared-types/typescript
  -> apps/frontend

services/agent
  -> packages/shared-types/python
  -> providers/tools/persistence/events

apps/frontend
  -> packages/shared-types/typescript
  -> services/agent over HTTP/SSE
  -> apps/desktop through Tauri IPC bridge

apps/desktop
  -> crates/hotpath
  -> bundled services/agent sidecar binary

crates/hotpath
  -> standalone Rust helper library/CLI
```

Disallowed direction:

```text
packages/shared-types -> apps/frontend
packages/shared-types -> services/agent runtime logic
crates/hotpath -> apps/frontend
services/agent -> apps/frontend
apps/desktop -> apps/frontend/src internals
scripts -> runtime imports
```

---

## 7. Generated Artifact Rules

Generated artifacts must be obvious.

Allowed generated/binary areas today:

- `apps/desktop/binaries`
- `apps/desktop/gen`
- `packages/shared-types/typescript/src/index.ts`
- test reports under temp/report folders
- build outputs such as `dist`, `target`, cache folders

Rules:

- Generated source that is committed must say where it comes from.
- Generated source must have a command that regenerates it.
- Generated source must not be hand-edited unless explicitly documented.
- Cache folders must not be used as source.
- Build outputs must not be architecture inputs.
- Temporary test output must stay out of source planning.

Recommended future generated layout:

```text
generated/
- reports/
- screenshots/
- schema/
- test-output/
```

Only create this folder if generated outputs keep spreading.

