## 9. Future Extraction Candidates

Do not extract now. Prepare only.

### Candidate: `packages/shared-types`

Possible future repo:

```text
zoc-shared-schema
```

Extract only if:

- multiple products consume the same schema
- schema versioning is stable
- generated TS/Python packages can be released independently

### Candidate: `crates/hotpath`

Possible future repo:

```text
zoc-hotpath
```

Extract only if:

- hotpath becomes useful outside Zoc AI
- CLI has stable JSON I/O
- Rust release pipeline is independent

### Candidate: `services/agent`

Possible future repo:

```text
zoc-agent-sidecar
```

Extract only if:

- API contracts are versioned
- sidecar can release independently
- desktop can consume sidecar versions safely

### Candidate: `apps/frontend`

Possible future repo:

```text
zoc-frontend
```

Extract only if:

- frontend can build against published shared packages
- desktop shell can consume a frontend build artifact
- local development remains easy

### Candidate: `apps/desktop`

Possible future repo:

```text
zoc-desktop-shell
```

Extract only if:

- bundled sidecar and hotpath versions are published artifacts
- Tauri release pipeline is independent
- frontend build artifact is published or injected

