## 11. Anti-Patterns

Avoid:

- creating `packages/*` just to make the repo look more modular
- moving feature code away from its owning feature too early
- importing backend internals into frontend code
- importing frontend state into shared packages
- making desktop IPC broad enough to bypass permission/trust rules
- treating generated caches as source
- putting long-lived product logic in `scripts`
- duplicating API shape definitions in frontend and backend
- adding tests without clear owner package
- hiding release-critical steps outside `scripts` or root commands

