## 14. Acceptance Checklist For Future Agents

Before adding or moving architecture files:

- Read `MONOREPO_ARCHITECTURE.md`.
- Read this file.
- Identify the owner zone.
- Confirm the change follows dependency direction rules.
- Confirm source and generated artifacts are not mixed.
- Confirm new shared packages have real reuse.
- Confirm no public API shape is duplicated across languages.
- Confirm package-local tests are added when behavior changes.
- Confirm root checks still work for cross-package changes.

Before creating a new package:

- It has at least one real consumer.
- It has a stable public surface.
- It has a package-local validation command.
- It does not import app-specific state.
- It does not hide ownership from the original feature.

Before extracting to a separate repo:

- The package has stable versioning.
- The package has independent CI.
- The package has clear release artifacts.
- The current monorepo release can consume those artifacts.
- The extraction reduces complexity instead of increasing it.

